Connect to the Palo Alto Networks device using SSH or console access.

Enter the command "request system software check" to check if any software updates are available.

If a software update is available, enter the command "request system software download version 8.1.X" to download the software to the
device. Replace "8.1.X" with the specific version number of the software update you want to download.

After the software is downloaded, enter the command "request system software install version 8.1.X" to install the software update. Again,
replace "8.1.X" with the specific version number of the software update you want to install.

The device will reboot automatically after the software installation is complete.
